content: great update. amazing new lighting & shadow features. also, lots of performance optimizations. I can now run with no jerkiness at max setting and single CPU core on galaxy s8. This is the BEST live wallpaper in the history of all live wallpapers.
I have a Note 9, a powerful phone and this app is lagging. How this can be explained? Edit: after latest update it runs smooth as as it should. Simply magic.
replyContent:
Good question. I know that in at least two cases, turning OFF the 'Use multiple CPU cores' option (Animation settings tab) helped. Apparently, multicore computation optimization does more harm than good on some devices. Please try this out.

Also, an update is coming today that should lower the CPU load required by the app.
